Description: Slightly concave lip sherd, thickened at rim, of Attic black-glazed pottery cup, probably a band-cup; wholly glazed save for line at top of rim on interior; incised graffito on the outside.
Bibliographic references: Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (pl. 22.2.21)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1459)
